00:15:50,782 --> 00:15:55,053
He was special. And you're as good
as your talent you work with.

229
00:15:55,086 --> 00:15:57,456
And Muhammad made me shine.

230
00:15:59,457 --> 00:16:01,426
This is BBC Television.

231
00:16:01,459 --> 00:16:03,095
Well, no doubt
about the top feature

232
00:16:03,128 --> 00:16:05,664
in tonight's specially lengthened
edition of Sportsview,

233
00:16:05,697 --> 00:16:07,499
because everyone
is still talking

234
00:16:07,532 --> 00:16:11,436
about the fight between Cassius
Clay and Henry Cooper.

235
00:16:11,469 --> 00:16:13,705
I knew the English pub were
tremendous.

236
00:16:13,738 --> 00:16:18,643
I knew for a fact they weren't
gonna like him the first time,

237
00:16:18,676 --> 00:16:20,079
'cause he talked too much.

238
00:16:24,749 --> 00:16:27,319
I knew they
wouldn't like Muhammad.

239
00:16:27,352 --> 00:16:33,592
When we first went there, we didn't see
nobody. The people didn't like him.

240
00:16:33,625 --> 00:16:39,564
And we're fighting the hero, Henry Cooper.
And he'd gone, "Five. Five."

241
00:16:39,597 --> 00:16:43,668
People didn't go for that, you know?
But he was just having fun.

242
00:16:43,701 --> 00:16:47,139
And Cassius Clay,
the gimmick man to the last,

243
00:16:47,172 --> 00:16:49,708
comes into the ring with this
monster crown on his head

244
00:16:49,741 --> 00:16:51,510
and all the way
down to the ringside,

245
00:16:51,543 --> 00:16:54,479
through the rows of people
with umbrellas,

246
00:16:54,512 --> 00:16:57,783
People were throwing things and trying
to knock the crown off his head.

247
00:16:57,816 --> 00:17:00,719
So here we go.
It's the fight of the year.

248
00:17:00,752 --> 00:17:03,755
Clay from the right-hand corner
against Cooper of Britain.

249
00:17:03,788 --> 00:17:08,627
And Clay has said, "I'll beat
him in five." We'll see.

250
00:17:15,967 --> 00:17:19,438
And Cooper's left eye is
a very sorry sight indeed.

251
00:17:19,471 --> 00:17:23,442
- And he's teasing Cooper.
- Round four.

252
00:17:23,475 --> 00:17:26,845
Henry Cooper, you know,
was well loved by everybody.

253
00:17:26,878 --> 00:17:30,582
I can see why.
And, it was a great night.

254
00:17:30,615 --> 00:17:33,685
After all,
he hit my guy on the chin.

255
00:17:37,522 --> 00:17:40,826
Dropped him. He slid down the ropes.
It was dramatic.

256
00:17:40,859 --> 00:17:43,095
And thank God
the ropes were there.

257
00:17:43,128 --> 00:17:45,397
That was the end
of the fourth round.

258
00:17:45,430 --> 00:17:48,100
And he hit him about two seconds
before the end of the round.

259
00:17:48,133 --> 00:17:50,602
He came back to the corner
and I was chewing him up.

260
00:17:50,635 --> 00:17:52,871
They're working furiously
on him in the corner.

261
00:17:52,904 --> 00:17:56,442
Angelo Dundee, his trainer, he
really is giving him a talking-to.

262
00:17:57,709 --> 00:18:00,178
Cooper's left
hook finally scores

263
00:18:00,211 --> 00:18:05,417
and Clay was down two seconds
from the end of the fourth round.

264
00:18:06,135 --> 00:18:07,820
And out they
come for round five.

265
00:18:07,853 --> 00:18:10,555
And now he's stepping in, and I
think this is it for Cooper.

266
00:18:10,588 --> 00:18:13,558
The towel has come in
from Cooper's corner.

267
00:18:13,591 --> 00:18:16,595
There was no alternative.
He had to stop the fight.

268
00:18:16,628 --> 00:18:21,733
Inside, Frank Butler asked Clay if he
still thought Henry Cooper was a bum.

269
00:18:21,766 --> 00:18:26,738
He's not a bum. I must admit, I
really underestimated the fella.

270
00:18:26,771 --> 00:18:30,709
My nose has never bled
until I fought him

271
00:18:30,742 --> 00:18:35,180
and his left hook was as good or
better than the people had predicted.

272
00:18:35,213 --> 00:18:38,550
And I must say he had me on the floor
at the end of the fourth round.

273
00:18:38,583 --> 00:18:39,951
I've never...
I've been on the floor once,

274
00:18:39,985 --> 00:18:44,723
but I wasn't really shook like I was.
And I have to say he's the...

275
00:18:44,756 --> 00:18:48,460
He really should be the
number-two contender next to me.

276
00:18:48,493 --> 00:18:50,495
After all,
I'm still the greatest.

277
00:18:50,528 --> 00:18:54,566
But he should have been the number-two
contender. He's the best I've met yet.

278
00:18:54,599 --> 00:18:56,001
Well, you're still
a wonderful prophet,

279
00:18:56,034 --> 00:18:59,771
because you said you'd win in round
five and you won in round five.

280
00:18:59,804 --> 00:19:03,842
But don't you think you were just a
little lucky to win in round five,

281
00:19:03,875 --> 00:19:05,877
in view of the fourth round?

282
00:19:05,910 --> 00:19:08,213
Well, I don't know
what you mean by luck.

283
00:19:08,246 --> 00:19:10,882
I told you it would end in
five and that's what happened.

284
00:19:10,915 --> 00:19:14,486
Yes, and you came in the ring
with a crown on your head.

285
00:19:14,519 --> 00:19:16,922
- Is that because...
- Because I am the king.

286
00:19:16,955 --> 00:19:20,482
I understand you have a Queen of
England, but you don't have a king.

287
00:19:22,586 --> 00:19:25,797
The second time we went, though,
we couldn't walk the streets.

288
00:19:25,830 --> 00:19:31,703
So there you go. I mean, then he
wasn't as glib or crazy or anything,

289
00:19:31,736 --> 00:19:35,631
but the people fell in love with him
because they knew it, he was for real.

290
00:19:39,644 --> 00:19:43,782
Maryum, what do people say? Do
they know you're my daughter?

291
00:19:43,815 --> 00:19:45,250
Yes, everybody.

292
00:19:45,283 --> 00:19:47,786
Tell me the truth.
Do they make any cracks?

293
00:19:47,819 --> 00:19:49,721
"You think you're cool
'cause of your daddy."

294
00:19:49,754 --> 00:19:54,759
Yeah, like, if I do
something, they say,

295
00:19:54,792 --> 00:19:58,530
"You think you're big just because
you're Muhammad Ali's daughter."

296
00:19:58,563 --> 00:20:02,534
They say that to you?
Who say it? Boys or girls?

297
00:20:02,567 --> 00:20:04,803
- Mostly boys.
- Oh.

298
00:20:05,937 --> 00:20:07,539
I mean, I knew he was famous

299
00:20:07,572 --> 00:20:10,308
as soon as I can walk and talk
and understand words.

300
00:20:10,341 --> 00:20:12,978
You know, I heard how
much people adored him

301
00:20:13,011 --> 00:20:15,847
and, you know, a simple trip
to the convenience store

302
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:20,685
was 50 people surrounding our car.
He couldn't go anywhere.

303
00:20:20,718 --> 00:20:22,838
And my father loved people,
so he would entertain them

304
00:20:22,854 --> 00:20:26,825
and stay out there and talk to 'em and,
"He's gonna get knocked down in five."

305
00:20:26,858 --> 00:20:29,361
And I'm sitting here looking at
him and I'm looking at the people

306
00:20:29,394 --> 00:20:33,698
and so I knew this is not normal.
You know what I'm saying?

307
00:20:33,731 --> 00:20:38,303
So I knew really, really
young, um, how huge he was,

308
00:20:38,336 --> 00:20:42,841
is when I would see people on television
that I admire, like Tom Jones,

309
00:20:42,874 --> 00:20:46,911
or Philip Wilson or Sly Stone,
Sammy Davis, Jr.,

310
00:20:46,944 --> 00:20:48,980
and then they would be at my house.
I'm like, "Whoa."

311
00:20:49,013 --> 00:20:53,418
You know, "You're famous," you
know, so I knew he was up there.

312
00:20:54,886 --> 00:20:59,658
My dad played kind of the good cop
out of the parents, you know.

313
00:20:59,691 --> 00:21:01,226
You know, it was so funny.

314
00:21:01,259 --> 00:21:05,330
He would, like, if I acted up, he'll go,
"Belinda, go, she needs a spanking."

315
00:21:05,363 --> 00:21:08,066
And then, you know, my mother
give me a little spanking.

316
00:21:08,099 --> 00:21:09,868
And he'll go in your room,
"Are you OK?"

317
00:21:09,901 --> 00:21:11,636
"You want me to get you
some ice cream?"

318
00:21:11,669 --> 00:21:13,705
You know. He always had
to be the nice guy,

319
00:21:13,738 --> 00:21:16,808
but he was just a practical joker.
Loved to joke.

320
00:21:16,841 --> 00:21:19,878
He just always played around,
very loving, very affectionate.

321
00:21:19,911 --> 00:21:21,031
Always kissing your cheeks.

322
00:21:21,046 --> 00:21:23,648
He'd wake you up in the
morning kissing your cheeks.

323
00:21:23,681 --> 00:21:26,685
"Gimme jaws, gimme the nose," you know.
So he was very loving

324
00:21:26,718 --> 00:21:30,722
and you would think a boxer
wouldn't be a teddy bear like that.

325
00:21:30,755 --> 00:21:33,625
I just had fun with my dad. I
always wanted to be with him.

326
00:21:33,658 --> 00:21:34,926
I was like a daddy's girl.

327
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:38,330
Daddy's gotta leave. He's going
into training, do you hear?

328
00:21:38,363 --> 00:21:41,399
- Daddy's going to fight.
- I want to go with you.

329
00:21:41,432 --> 00:21:44,803
You wanna go with me? You can't.
Can you fight?

330
00:21:46,037 --> 00:21:49,641
Do you fight? No, you don't fight.
You can't go.

331
00:21:49,674 --> 00:21:52,010
- Here you go.
- Yes, I go!

332
00:21:52,043 --> 00:21:55,647
No, Daddy going to get in shape
and you stay at home. You hear?

333
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:58,483
I wanna...
I wanna go with you.

334
00:21:58,516 --> 00:22:01,086
You wanna go fight with me?
OK.

335
00:22:02,420 --> 00:22:05,890
- Come on, sweetheart.
- The man gonna fight!

336
00:22:05,923 --> 00:22:08,360
- Who gonna fight?
- The man.

337
00:22:08,393 --> 00:22:10,429
The man? Your dad.

338
00:22:14,132 --> 00:22:16,801
Would you please
cook me some dinner?

339
00:22:16,834 --> 00:22:20,405
I go to work all day,
I've been out all day

340
00:22:20,438 --> 00:22:24,809
and when all you have to do is to lay
around in this big house and live easy

341
00:22:24,842 --> 00:22:27,078
and at least you can
have my meal on time.

342
00:22:27,111 --> 00:22:30,682
- Woman, please, is the food ready?
- Yes.

343
00:22:30,715 --> 00:22:33,118
All right. Come on.
Let's go eat, May May.

344
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:38,423
There's one thing you don't mess
with is colored folks' food

345
00:22:38,456 --> 00:22:39,991
and colored folks' money.

346
00:22:41,859 --> 00:22:43,228
Come on. Come on, darlin'.

347
00:22:47,732 --> 00:22:50,101
He loved his children.

348
00:22:50,134 --> 00:22:53,705
He loved his children,
but he was a blessed man

349
00:22:53,738 --> 00:22:58,042
to have Belinda's mom and dad
take care of the kids

350
00:22:58,075 --> 00:23:02,714
when there was such a demand put
on him as being a world man.

351
00:23:02,747 --> 00:23:08,987
He asked to travel here or travel there
so his title, his heavyweight belt...

352
00:23:09,020 --> 00:23:12,424
What was more valuable
than that heavyweight belt

353
00:23:12,457 --> 00:23:17,061
was having his mother-in-law raising
the children, which she did.

354
00:23:17,094 --> 00:23:19,564
And she did a good job.

355
00:23:21,499 --> 00:23:24,736
He used to love
to tape record conversations

356
00:23:24,769 --> 00:23:27,138
and he would always say,
"I'm gonna tape you guys,

357
00:23:27,171 --> 00:23:31,009
and when you're older you're
gonna love this, these tapes."

358
00:23:31,042 --> 00:23:34,746
And, um, he would always do it
so when my parents got divorced,

359
00:23:34,779 --> 00:23:37,015
he would call me. "How you doing?
What are you doing?"

360
00:23:37,048 --> 00:23:38,483
"What do you wanna be
when you grow up?"

361
00:23:38,516 --> 00:23:42,821
He would always tell me time is gonna
fly, you know, I'm gonna be older.

362
00:23:42,854 --> 00:23:45,089
I mean, he was just, like...
he could foresee things

363
00:23:45,122 --> 00:23:47,438
and knew how important
those things would be.

364
00:23:47,959 --> 00:23:49,227
- Maryum?
- Sir?

365
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:53,131
You're now 11 years old. Now,
do you wanna go to college?

366
00:23:53,164 --> 00:23:56,167
Yes, sir. Now, what do
you wanna do there?

367
00:23:56,200 --> 00:24:00,205
Everything Allah made has a purpose.
Trees have a purpose.

368
00:24:00,238 --> 00:24:04,008
- What's the purpose of a cow?
- To give us milk.

369
00:24:04,041 --> 00:24:06,811
OK. What's
the purpose of the sun?

370
00:24:06,844 --> 00:24:09,781
- The sun?
- Sun.

371
00:24:09,814 --> 00:24:15,787
- To give us light and heat.
- And make things grow.

372
00:24:15,820 --> 00:24:20,091
So everything God made, the cows,
horses, the moon, stars, ants,

373
00:24:20,124 --> 00:24:21,993
everything has a purpose.

374
00:24:22,026 --> 00:24:24,262
Now, what's your purpose?
You're a human being.

375
00:24:24,295 --> 00:24:28,032
If God made the sun have a purpose,
humans have a purpose too.

376
00:24:28,065 --> 00:24:31,002
Hey, you haven't found your
life purpose yet, have you?

377
00:24:31,035 --> 00:24:32,470
Yes.

378
00:24:32,503 --> 00:24:35,840
If everybody's born for a purpose,
what do you think you were born for?

379
00:24:35,873 --> 00:24:40,278
- To make people feel better.
- To fix people up.

380
00:24:40,311 --> 00:24:43,048
That's good.
That's good, Maryum.

381
00:24:52,590 --> 00:24:59,564
This bout, 15 rounds for the
heavyweight championship of the world.

382
00:24:59,597 --> 00:25:06,004
The challenger from Louisville,
Kentucky, Cassius Clay.

383
00:25:06,037 --> 00:25:10,108
And his opponent
from Denver, Colorado,

384
00:25:10,141 --> 00:25:18,116
the heavyweight champion of the
world, Charles Sonny Liston.

385
00:25:18,149 --> 00:25:22,587
Ali, by then, had had
19 professional fights.

386
00:25:22,620 --> 00:25:25,323
It wasn't as though he'd
suddenly come upon the scene.

387
00:25:25,356 --> 00:25:28,993
He'd been properly,
properly managed

388
00:25:29,026 --> 00:25:33,998
in the sense that, Dundee
was an expert match maker.

389
00:25:34,031 --> 00:25:37,869
I mean, match making is one of
the great skills in boxing.

390
00:25:37,902 --> 00:25:39,955
Finding the right
guy at the right time.

391
00:25:43,908 --> 00:25:47,612
- Sonny Liston was a gangster.
- I mean, he was a mob guy.

392
00:25:47,645 --> 00:25:52,918
He had fast hands and he could punch.
You wouldn't take him lightly.

393
00:25:55,953 --> 00:26:00,658
Nobody gave, Ali, or Clay
as he then was, a chance.

394
00:26:00,691 --> 00:26:04,262
Liston will kill him.
Kill him in the first round.

395
00:26:05,663 --> 00:26:07,999
It'll be Liston in three rounds.

396
00:26:08,032 --> 00:26:10,902
- Liston.
- One, Liston.

397
00:26:10,935 --> 00:26:13,338
- Second round, Liston.
- Liston in four.

398
00:26:13,371 --> 00:26:15,273
Liston!

399
00:26:15,306 --> 00:26:18,309
- Well, I am for Liston.
- Who did this guy ever fight?

400
00:26:18,342 --> 00:26:19,377
- Who?
- Yeah.

401
00:26:19,410 --> 00:26:20,578
- Clay?
- Yeah.

402
00:26:20,611 --> 00:26:28,019
I mean, what Ali set out to
do was to get into his head.

403
00:26:28,052 --> 00:26:32,090
And, you know,
it had occurred to Ali,

404
00:26:32,123 --> 00:26:37,061
I think, that,
Liston thought he was crazy.

405
00:26:37,094 --> 00:26:38,630
That Ali was crazy.

406
00:26:40,431 --> 00:26:43,668
- You ain't got a chance!
- Let us see, let us see.

407
00:26:47,238 --> 00:26:50,241
Liston, he can't deal with this.

408
00:26:50,274 --> 00:26:53,144
A fella coming at him with a
sledgehammer, he could deal with it,

409
00:26:53,177 --> 00:26:56,247
but, well, "This fella's
crazy," you know.

410
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:58,149
And that's how he
went into the ring.

411
00:26:58,182 --> 00:26:59,751
Hey, get back!

412
00:27:04,789 --> 00:27:09,694
I predict that tonight somebody will
die at the ringside from shock.

413
00:27:09,727 --> 00:27:13,231
The world heavyweight boxing
title on the line.

414
00:27:13,264 --> 00:27:17,068
Looking to get Sonny to lunge.

415
00:27:17,101 --> 00:27:19,037
Liston thought he was
gonna win the fight

416
00:27:19,070 --> 00:27:22,106
and his people thought
he was gonna win the fight,

417
00:27:22,139 --> 00:27:24,208
but,
um, that wasn't what Ali saw.

418
00:27:24,241 --> 00:27:27,712
Less than one minute more
in this second round.

419
00:27:29,213 --> 00:27:32,116
Another downright hammer shot.
There goes another one!

420
00:27:32,149 --> 00:27:34,686
Sonny wobbles. Got a wobble.

421
00:27:48,766 --> 00:27:51,469
The fight never went
Liston's way.

422
00:27:51,502 --> 00:27:55,339
At the end of the sixth round,
Liston sat on the stool and said,

423
00:27:55,372 --> 00:27:57,175
"That's it, I've finished."

424
00:27:57,208 --> 00:27:58,810
They might be stopping it.

425
00:27:58,843 --> 00:28:00,478
That might be over,
ladies and gentlemen.

426
00:28:00,511 --> 00:28:04,315
Get up there, Joe, get up there.
Get up in the ring.

427
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:13,624
Get near the microphone.

428
00:28:13,657 --> 00:28:18,029
All you reporters... all you
reporters made it hard on Liston.

429
00:28:18,062 --> 00:28:20,832
Never write about me like that.
Never make me six to one.

430
00:28:20,865 --> 00:28:24,469
You just make me angry. Never,
never make me no underdog,

431
00:28:24,502 --> 00:28:27,038
and never talk
about who's gonna stop me.

432
00:28:27,071 --> 00:28:28,773
Ain't nobody gonna stop me.

433
00:28:28,806 --> 00:28:31,442
No heavyweight in the world's
fast enough to stop me.

434
00:28:31,475 --> 00:28:35,813
- Who's the greatest?
- Who you gonna fight next?

435
00:28:39,250 --> 00:28:42,320
Float like a butterfly,
sting like a bee.

436
00:28:42,353 --> 00:28:45,456
Float like a butterfly,
sting like a bee.

437
00:28:45,489 --> 00:28:48,059
Float like a butterfly,
sting like a bee.

438
00:28:48,092 --> 00:28:50,328
Float like a butterfly,
sting like a bee.

439
00:28:50,361 --> 00:28:53,831
Say, "Float like a butterfly,
sting like a bee."

440
00:28:56,567 --> 00:29:00,505
- Sting like a fly like a bee.
- Who's your daddy?

441
00:29:03,874 --> 00:29:05,209
Say it. Say it for Daddy.

442
00:29:05,242 --> 00:29:07,512
Float like a bee,
sting like a bee.

443
00:29:07,545 --> 00:29:11,316
- What's your daddy's name?
- Muhammad Ali!

444
00:29:16,153 --> 00:29:19,090
Why do you insist on being
called Muhammad Ali now?

445
00:29:19,123 --> 00:29:21,125
That's the name given to me
by my leading teacher,

446
00:29:21,158 --> 00:29:23,795
the Honorable Elijah Muhammad.
That's my original name.

447
00:29:23,828 --> 00:29:26,097
That's a black man name. Cassius
Clay was my slave name.

448
00:29:26,130 --> 00:29:29,133
- I'm no longer a slave.
- What does it mean?

449
00:29:29,166 --> 00:29:32,904
Muhammad means "worthy of all
praises," and Ali means "most high."

450
00:29:33,738 --> 00:29:35,738
Do you intend to
fight under that name?

451
00:29:35,740 --> 00:29:38,876
Yes, sir. I wanna be called by that name.
I write autographs with that name.

