00:57:04,119 --> 00:57:05,988
- No, you don't.
- Yes, I do!

820
00:57:06,021 --> 00:57:07,156
Let me hear you.

821
00:57:07,189 --> 00:57:11,027
A, B, C, D, E, F, G

822
00:57:11,060 --> 00:57:14,764
Oh, wa, go, go, L, M, N, O, P

823
00:57:14,797 --> 00:57:17,900
Q, R, S, T, U, V

824
00:57:17,933 --> 00:57:21,471
W, X, Y and Z

825
00:57:21,504 --> 00:57:24,974
Now I know my ABCs

826
00:57:25,007 --> 00:57:28,110
Won't you come and play with me?

827
00:57:28,143 --> 00:57:31,781
Hey, hey. Ooh, I
love you, Muhammad.

828
00:57:31,814 --> 00:57:37,120
I just love you so much. I think
about you every day. I miss you.

829
00:57:42,892 --> 00:57:46,529
It doesn't come to me
as him being famous.

830
00:57:46,562 --> 00:57:50,066
He's being Dad.
It really didn't faze me any

831
00:57:50,099 --> 00:57:54,270
because I feel like everybody
else, like Dad is Dad.

832
00:57:54,303 --> 00:57:58,040
I grew up with Rasheda,
Jamillah and Maryum.

833
00:57:58,073 --> 00:58:03,613
We was a close-knit family and we
knew about our other siblings.

834
00:58:03,646 --> 00:58:07,884
We would go, like, say we had summer
or winter break out of school,

835
00:58:07,917 --> 00:58:11,554
we would go to California where
he stayed at the Fremont Place

